I've never made brownies (although I do cook/bake a lot). I used powdered unsweetened cocoa in this recipe and found these to be GREAT brownies! Somewhere along the line, I inherited 2 cans of cocoa (from departing seasonals) and wanted to use it up. So, here's what I did with the cocoa in lieu of the bittersweet chocolate: to substitute cocoa powder for bittersweet chocolate, use 25% less chocolate, and 1.5 tsp more sugar per ounce of chocolate used. This translates to about 1 3/4 cup cocoa, 6 Tbsp vegetable oil, and 3 Tbsp. sugar. I used the remaining listed ingredients as called for. Because I am at high altitude (8,200 ft), I increased the oven temp 25 degrees to 375F, and baked 35-40 minutes for fudgy brownies. I think I will make them again...yum......

